10. The Leetztonary of luxeuil.

This manuscript, numbered 9427 in the Bibliotheque Nationale, contains the lections of the Mass for the ecclesiastical year. It is written in minuscules of the seventh century. Mabillon found it at the Abbey of Luxeuil, and published it in his De Lituryz'a Gallicana. He did not give the complete text, as he did not consider it necessary to reproduce, in their entirety, the portions known from other sources. He therefore prints merely the beginning and end of each lection, with the necessary references, but he gives the whole of the rubrics, which are of much greater importance.
